clears
Homonym Number: 1
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the clears, the mainly fern-covered peaty land on Chatham Island, open or barren peat country; usu. collective pl. the clears.
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
